I have faced the same problem when I was working with an [Ant][1] script to build my application.

I use [Eclipse][2] for my application development, and I changed the compiler version in build properties of the project. But that didn&#39;t work for me. Then I found out that I can provide the compiler version in the Ant script.

I modified the Ant script at the section where it compile Java files.

    &lt;target name=&quot;build-java&quot; depends=&quot;prepare-build&quot;&gt;
        &lt;echo message=&quot;Compiling java files&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;javac ....
               target=&quot;1.5&quot;...
        &lt;/javac&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

This worked for me to resolve the unsupported major minor issue.

  [1]: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Ant
  [2]: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eclipse_%28software%29

If you&#39;re facing this issue while using [Maven](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Maven), you can compile your code using the plug-in [Maven Compiler](http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-compiler-plugin/examples/set-compiler-source-and-target.html).


     &lt;build&gt;
            &lt;plugins&gt;
                &lt;plugin&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                    &lt;version&gt;3.1&lt;/version&gt;
                    &lt;configuration&gt;
                        &lt;source&gt;1.6&lt;/source&gt;
                        &lt;target&gt;1.6&lt;/target&gt;
                    &lt;/configuration&gt;
                &lt;/plugin&gt;
           .....

UPDATE: set `source` and `target` to `1.8`, if you are using JDK 8.

