If you follow the link https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2 and search for them you won&#39;t find them --&gt; https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/
You can always check Maven Repository Sites like https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.xerces/org.apache.xerces to check for which version of an Artifact is available and where. 
For example your org.apache.xerces:org.apache.xerces:jar:2.12.2 is available only in the Clazzes repository: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.xerces/org.apache.xerces?repo=clazzes-maven

Apache-commons probably has the dependency bundled (you could check the maven Repository for that).

